{"timestamp": "2025-12-07 04:04:24.188661", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nSummary of Network Health\\n- Control plane: All EBGP sessions across the fabric (leaves, spines, super-spine) appear established and stable. Each spine shows full reachability to all advertised /24s; the super-spine is peering with all spines and reflecting routes appropriately.\\n- Data plane: Asymmetric behavior between two pods:\\n  - pc_0_1 (10.0.1.2) has normal local gateway reachability and end-to-end connectivity.\\n  - pc_0_0 (10.0.0.2) cannot reach its local gateway (10.0.0.1), and is unreachable from other hosts.\\n\\nObserved Symptoms\\n- pc_0_0:\\n  - Fails to ping its default gateway 10.0.0.1 (100% loss).\\n  - ARP cache on pc_0_0 contains the gateway MAC (state DELAY), suggesting ARP resolution occurred at least once.\\n- leaf_router_0_0 (gateway for 10.0.0.0/24):\\n  - Interface eth8 is up with 10.0.0.1/24; ethtool reports link detected.\\n  - ARP from leaf to 10.0.0.2 succeeds (arping returns replies), confirming L2 connectivity to pc_0_0.\\n  - ICMP echo replies to pc_0_0 do not get sent (pc still sees 100% loss).\\n  - Kernel routing table includes a blackhole route for 10.0.0.0/24, and does not show a standard connected route for 10.0.0.0/24 via eth8.\\n- pc_0_1 and leaf_router_0_1:\\n  - pc_0_1 successfully pings its gateway 10.0.1.1.\\n  - leaf_router_0_1 routing table correctly shows connected 10.0.1.0/24 on eth8 (no blackhole route present).\\n\\nControl-Plane Verification\\n- BGP:\\n  - leaf_router_0_0 (AS 65200) “show ip bgp summary”: 8 neighbors up, receiving 31 prefixes from each, advertising expected networks (network 10.0.0.0/24 configured).\\n  - leaf_router_0_1 (AS 65201): similar healthy BGP status (network 10.0.1.0/24 configured).\\n  - spines and super-spine: all EBGP sessions established; ECMP to downstream prefixes visible; no signs of session flaps or withdrawal storms.\\n\\nData-Plane and FIB Findings\\n- leaf_router_0_0 FRR RIB shows both:\\n  - Connected 10.0.0.0/24 via eth8, and\\n  - A kernel blackhole entry for 10.0.0.0/24.\\n- Linux kernel (ip route) on leaf_router_0_0 shows:\\n  - blackhole 10.0.0.0/24 (no connected route listed for this prefix).\\n- Consequence: Any IP packet sourced from leaf_router_0_0 destined to 10.0.0.0/24 (including ICMP replies to pc_0_0) is dropped by the kernel blackhole route, despite L2 adjacency being fine (as proven by ARP success).\\n- Contrast: leaf_router_0_1 has a normal connected route for 10.0.1.0/24 and no blackhole entry; pc_0_1 therefore operates normally.\\n\\nFault Localization\\n- Fault domain: Leaf L3 forwarding for subnet 10.0.0.0/24.\\n- Faulty device: leaf_router_0_0.\\n- Non-faulty/healthy: leaf_router_0_1, spines, super-spine, and the broader EBGP control plane.\\n\\nRoot Cause\\n- An unintended blackhole route for 10.0.0.0/24 is installed in the kernel FIB on leaf_router_0_0. This route suppresses normal L3 forwarding to directly connected hosts on eth8, causing the router to drop responses to pc_0_0 and to drop any IP traffic to that subnet. L2/ARP is healthy; the failure is strictly at the L3 FIB level.\\n- The condition is specific to leaf_router_0_0 (not present on leaf_router_0_1), consistent with the observed per-pod impact.\\n\\nImpact Assessment\\n- pc_0_0 has no IP connectivity (cannot reach default gateway; unreachable from elsewhere).\\n- All other tested subnets/paths remain reachable through the fabric as per the BGP and reachability checks.\\n\\nEvidence (key excerpts)\\n- pc_0_0:\\n  - ip route: default via 10.0.0.1 dev eth0\\n  - ping 10.0.0.1 → 100% loss; neighbor entry for 10.0.0.1 present with MAC.\\n- leaf_router_0_0:\\n  - ip addr eth8: 10.0.0.1/24, link detected yes.\\n  - ip route: blackhole 10.0.0.0/24; no connected route shown for 10.0.0.0/24.\\n  - arping 10.0.0.2 → replies received (L2 OK).\\n  - eth8 counters show RX increments with minimal TX (consistent with drops of IP replies).\\n- leaf_router_0_1:\\n  - ip route includes normal connected route: 10.0.1.0/24 dev eth8 proto kernel scope link src 10.0.1.1.\\n  - pc_0_1 → 10.0.1.1 ping success.\\n\\nConclusion\\n- The network’s control plane is healthy; the data plane issue is localized to leaf_router_0_0.\\n- The abnormal, incorrect blackhole route for 10.0.0.0/24 on leaf_router_0_0 is the root cause preventing pc_0_0 from communicating with its gateway and the rest of the network., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='06b71b8d-26aa-452b-9bf5-8fab82ed7e8c'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
